Deemed consent
Without limiting subsection (2) and subject to subsection (9), an individual (P) who provides personal data to an organisation (A) with a view to P entering into a contract with A is deemed to consent to the following where reasonably necessary for the conclusion of the contract between P and A:
(a) the disclosure of that personal data by A to another organisation (B);
(b) the collection and use of that personal data by B;
(c) the disclosure of that personal data by B to another organisation.

